ENCEPHALITIS - INDIA (UTTAR PRADESH)
**********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>

Date: Sat 21 Aug 1999
From: ProMED-mail <promed@usa.healthnet.org>
Source: Times of India Tue 17 Aug 1999 [edited]

Encephalitis claims 15 lives
--------------------------------------
GORAKHPUR: Encephalitis has claimed the lives of 15 persons here since 3 Aug
1999. As many as 90 persons were admitted to the BRD Medical College, here
since the beginning of this month.
Some patients were discharged after treatment but on Monday there were 55
patients in encephalitis ward of the Nehru Hospital attached to medical
college. There is no record of deaths in private nursing homes. Dr Y D
Singh, head of paediatric department of the medical college said majority of
patients were between the age group of 5-8 years. On an average 5 patients
are being admitted per day in the medical college. The maximum number of
patients are coming from Kushinagar district followed by Gorakhpur.
Encephalitis first struck eastern Uttar Pradesh in 1978. According to
official records since then more than 4000 persons had died. The children
who survive after treatment normally become mentally retarded. The
occurrence time of disease is between September to December but this year
the disease had struck in August.
There is no testing laboratory in eastern Uttar Pradesh and till the results
of test comes, either patients die or are released from the hospital.
Vaccination is an effective step to prevent the disease but since the past 2
years it had been stopped for the reasons best known to government.
--
